    </div>
    <figcaption><span class="fig-num">Fig. 3</span>The coupling that compounds. The potential screens cheaply; the autonomous lab makes and measures the survivors; the measurements return as training data, so the next pass through the loop screens better. The potential is one part of an engine, not the engine.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>
    The compounding impact, then, is less "we found material X" and more a change in standing:
    computational triage crosses a threshold of trustworthiness where an experimentalist treats its
    ranking as a real prior, worth pointing a furnace at, rather than a suggestion to be ignored. It
    is the claim that holds up.
  </p>
</Primer>
